rks), which is recorded as  <i>Hothom</i> in 1285 and also appears rarely in surnames as  <i>Hothom</i> and  <i>Hothon</i> and commonly as   Hotham  ; or with ‘lands … called Hattom Bakelowe’ in Brewood (Staffs), 1588 in   Staffs Archives  . In Cornwall, possibly related to   Hotten  ."]},{"name":"Hotham","meanings":["English (East Yorkshire): habitational name usually from Hotham (East Yorkshire), but occasionally perhaps also from Holtham in Legsby (Lincolnshire). The East Yorkshire placename may derive from Old English <i>hōdum</i>, dative plural form of <i>hōd</i> ‘shelter’, while the origin of the Lincolnshire placename is uncertain. Compare   Holtham  ."]},{"name":"Hattem","meanings":["English:  see  Hattam  ."]},{"name":"Hotten","meanings":["English (mainly Cornwall): unexplained.","German (mainly <b>Hötten</b>): unexplained."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Hattam was born in 1515, in Chelmsford, Essex, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Anne Hattam. He died in 1561, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 46."},"et":{"1515–1561":"1515–1561","1510–1567":"1510–1567","1538–1592":"11.jaanuar1538kuni10.jaanuar1539–1592","1567":"1567","1510":"1510","1561":"1561","1592":"1592","1538":"11. jaanuar 1538 kuni 10. jaanuar 1539","1515":"1515","Chelmsford, Essex, England":"Chelmsford, Essex, England","Chelmsford, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Chelmsford, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1515–1561":"1515–1561","1510–1567":"1510–1567","1538–1592":"vuodesta11.tammikuuta1538vuoteen10.tammikuuta1539–1592","1567":"1567","1510":"1510","1561":"1561","1592":"1592","1538":"vuodesta 11. tammikuuta 1538 vuoteen 10. tammikuuta 1539","1515":"1515","Chelmsford, Essex, England":"Chelmsford, Essex, England","Chelmsford, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Chelmsford, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1515–1561":"1515–1561","1510–1567":"1510–1567","1538–1592":"du11janvier1538au10janvier1539–1592","1567":"1567","1510":"1510","1561":"1561","1592":"1592","1538":"du 11 janvier 1538 au 10 janvier 1539","1515":"1515","Chelmsford, Essex, England":"Chelmsford, Essex, Angleterre","Chelmsford, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Chelmsford, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert Hattam est né en 1515, à Chelmsford, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Anne Hattam. Il est décédé en 1561, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 46 ans."},"de":{"1515–1561":"1515–1561","1510–1567":"1510–1567","1538–1592":"von11.Januar1538bis10.Januar1539–1592","1567":"1567","1510":"1510","1561":"1561","1592":"1592","1538":"von 11. Januar 1538 bis 10. Januar 1539","1515":"1515","Chelmsford, Essex, England":"Chelmsford, Essex, England","Chelmsford, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Chelmsford, Essex, England, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"En